        "solution": "<b>Solution (EN):</b><br>Let the monthly salary of the man be S.<br>Payment towards debt = 50% of S = 0.5 S.<br>Remaining salary = S &minus; 0.5 S = 0.5 S.<br>He spends 25% of the remaining salary.<br>So, his savings = (100% &minus; 25%) = 75% of the remaining salary.<br>Savings = 75% of 0.5 S = 0.75 &times; 0.5 S = 0.375 S.<br>We are given that his savings = ₹546.<br>0.375 S = 546 &rArr; (3/8) S = 546<br>S = 546 &times; 8 / 3 = 182 &times; 8 = ₹1,456.<br><br><b>Solution (HI):</b><br>माना आदमी का मासिक वेतन S है।<br>ऋण का भुगतान = S का 50% = 0.5 S.<br>शेष वेतन = S &minus; 0.5 S = 0.5 S.<br>वह शेष वेतन का 25% खर्च करता है।<br>इसलिए, उसकी बचत = शेष वेतन का (100% &minus; 25%) = 75%.<br>बचत = 0.5 S का 75% = 0.75 &times; 0.5 S = 0.375 S.<br>हमें दिया गया है कि उसकी बचत = ₹546.<br>0.375 S = 546 &rArr; (3/8) S = 546<br>S = 546 &times; 8 / 3 = 182 &times; 8 = ₹1,456.<br><br><b>Short Trick:</b><br>Let total be 100%. Remaining after debt = 50%. Saving = 75% of 50% = 37.5% = 3/8 fraction.<br>If 3/8 = 546, then Total = 546 &times; (8 / 3) = 1456.",
