        "q_en": "A principal of ₹400 grows to ₹441 in 2 years at compound interest, compounded annually. If the rate of interest is increased by 5% per annum for the same duration, what will be the new amount?",
        "q_hi": "₹400 का मूलधन वार्षिक रूप से संयोजित चक्रवृद्धि ब्याज पर 2 वर्षों में ₹441 हो जाता है। यदि समान अवधि के लिए ब्याज दर में प्रति वर्ष 5% की वृद्धि की जाती है, तो नई राशि क्या होगी?",
        "section": "Arithmetical and Numerical Ability",
        "solution": "<b>Solution (EN):</b><br>Let the original rate of interest be R% per annum.<br>Using the formula A = P(1 + R/100)<sup>t</sup><br>441 = 400(1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup><br>441 / 400 = (1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup><br>(21 / 20)<sup>2</sup> = (1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup><br>1 + R/100 = 21 / 20 &rArr; R/100 = 1/20 &rArr; R = 5%.<br>New rate of interest = 5% + 5% = 10%.<br>New amount = 400(1 + 10/100)<sup>2</sup><br>= 400 &times; (11/10) &times; (11/10)<br>= 400 &times; 1.21 = ₹484.<br><br><b>Solution (HI):</b><br>माना मूल ब्याज दर R% प्रति वर्ष है।<br>सूत्र A = P(1 + R/100)<sup>t</sup> का उपयोग करने पर<br>441 = 400(1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup><br>441 / 400 = (1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup><br>(21 / 20)<sup>2</sup> = (1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup><br>1 + R/100 = 21 / 20 &rArr; R/100 = 1/20 &rArr; R = 5%.<br>ब्याज की नई दर = 5% + 5% = 10%.<br>नई राशि = 400(1 + 10/100)<sup>2</sup><br>= 400 &times; (11/10) &times; (11/10)<br>= 400 &times; 1.21 = ₹484.<br><br><b>Short Trick:</b><br>&radic;(441/400) = 21/20 &rArr; Initial Rate = 5%.<br>New rate = 10%. For 2 years at 10%, effective CI = 21%. Amount = 400 + 21% of 400 = 400 + 84 = ₹484.",
