        "q_en": "<img align=\"middle\" alt=\"What space is space the space equivalent space common space fraction space form space of space 0.1 with bar on top space plus 0.5 ?\" class=\"Wirisformula\" data-mathml=\"«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi»What«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»is«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»the«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»equivalent«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»common«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»fraction«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»form«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»of«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mn»0«/mn»«mo».«/mo»«mover»«mn»1«/mn»«mo»§#175;«/mo»«/mover»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mo»+«/mo»«mn»0«/mn»«mo».«/mo»«mn»5«/mn»«mo»?«/mo»«/math»\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"math\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"max-width: none;\">",
        "q_hi": "<img align=\"middle\" alt=\"What space is space the space equivalent space common space fraction space form space of space 0.1 with bar on top space plus 0.5 ?\" class=\"Wirisformula\" data-mathml=\"«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi»What«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»is«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»the«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»equivalent«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»common«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»fraction«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»form«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mi»of«/mi»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mn»0«/mn»«mo».«/mo»«mover»«mn»1«/mn»«mo»§#175;«/mo»«/mover»«mo»§#160;«/mo»«mo»+«/mo»«mn»0«/mn»«mo».«/mo»«mn»5«/mn»«mo»?«/mo»«/math»\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"math\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"max-width: none;\">",
        "section": "Arithmetical and Numerical Ability",
        "solution": "<b>Solution (EN):</b><br>We know that 0.1&#773; means 0.1111... which can be written as the fraction 1/9.<br>Also, 0.5 can be written as 1/2.<br>Now, add both fractions:<br>= 1/9 + 1/2<br>Taking the LCM of 9 and 2, which is 18:<br>= (2 + 9) / 18<br>= 11/18.<br><br><b>Solution (HI):</b><br>हम जानते हैं कि 0.1&#773; का अर्थ 0.1111... है जिसे भिन्न 1/9 के रूप में लिखा जा सकता है।<br>साथ ही, 0.5 को 1/2 लिखा जा सकता है।<br>अब, दोनों भिन्नों को जोड़ें:<br>= 1/9 + 1/2<br>9 और 2 का LCM लेने पर, जो 18 है:<br>= (2 + 9) / 18<br>= 11/18.<br><br><b>Short Trick:</b><br>0.1&#773; + 0.5 = 1/9 + 1/2 = (2+9)/18 = 11/18.",
