        "solution": "<b>Solution (EN):</b><br>First, express all the numbers in their prime factorization forms.<br>1st number: 3<sup>3</sup> &times; 7<sup>2</sup> &times; 12 = 3<sup>3</sup> &times; 7<sup>2</sup> &times; (2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3) = 2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup> &times; 7<sup>2</sup><br>2nd number: 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 12<sup>2</sup> &times; 16 = 3<sup>2</sup> &times; (2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3)<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> = 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> &times; 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> = 2<sup>8</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup><br>3rd number: 7<sup>3</sup> &times; 12<sup>2</sup> &times; 16<sup>2</sup> = 7<sup>3</sup> &times; (2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3)<sup>2</sup> &times; (2<sup>4</sup>)<sup>2</sup> = 7<sup>3</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> &times; 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>8</sup> = 2<sup>12</sup> &times; 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 7<sup>3</sup><br>To find the LCM, take the highest power of each prime factor present:<br>LCM = 2<sup>12</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup> &times; 7<sup>3</sup>.<br><br><b>Solution (HI):</b><br>सबसे पहले, सभी संख्याओं को उनके अभाज्य गुणनखंडन रूपों में व्यक्त करें।<br>पहली संख्या: 3<sup>3</sup> &times; 7<sup>2</sup> &times; 12 = 3<sup>3</sup> &times; 7<sup>2</sup> &times; (2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3) = 2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup> &times; 7<sup>2</sup><br>दूसरी संख्या: 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 12<sup>2</sup> &times; 16 = 3<sup>2</sup> &times; (2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3)<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> = 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> &times; 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> = 2<sup>8</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup><br>तीसरी संख्या: 7<sup>3</sup> &times; 12<sup>2</sup> &times; 16<sup>2</sup> = 7<sup>3</sup> &times; (2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3)<sup>2</sup> &times; (2<sup>4</sup>)<sup>2</sup> = 7<sup>3</sup> &times; 2<sup>4</sup> &times; 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 2<sup>8</sup> = 2<sup>12</sup> &times; 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 7<sup>3</sup><br>LCM ज्ञात करने के लिए, मौजूद प्रत्येक अभाज्य गुणनखंड की उच्चतम घात लें:<br>LCM = 2<sup>12</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup> &times; 7<sup>3</sup>.<br><br><b>Short Trick:</b><br>Decompose into primes:<br>1) 2<sup>2</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup> &times; 7<sup>2</sup><br>2) 2<sup>8</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup><br>3) 2<sup>12</sup> &times; 3<sup>2</sup> &times; 7<sup>3</sup><br>LCM = highest powers = 2<sup>12</sup> &times; 3<sup>4</sup> &times; 7<sup>3</sup>.",
