        "q_en": "Three ropes of lengths 84 m, 126 m, and 168 m are to be cut into equal pieces such that each piece is as long as possible. Find the maximum possible length of each piece.",
        "q_hi": "84 मीटर, 126 मीटर और 168 मीटर लंबाई की तीन रस्सियों को समान टुकड़ों में इस प्रकार काटा जाना है कि प्रत्येक टुकड़ा जितना संभव हो उतना लंबा हो। प्रत्येक टुकड़े की अधिकतम संभव लंबाई ज्ञात कीजिए।",
        "section": "Arithmetical and Numerical Ability",
        "solution": "<b>Solution (EN):</b><br>To find the maximum possible length of each piece, we need to calculate the Highest Common Factor (HCF) of 84, 126, and 168.<br>Prime factorization:<br>84 = 2 &times; 2 &times; 3 &times; 7<br>126 = 2 &times; 3 &times; 3 &times; 7<br>168 = 2 &times; 2 &times; 2 &times; 3 &times; 7<br>Common factors are 2, 3, and 7.<br>HCF = 2 &times; 3 &times; 7 = 42.<br>Thus, the maximum possible length of each piece is 42 m.<br><br><b>Solution (HI):</b><br>प्रत्येक टुकड़े की अधिकतम संभव लंबाई ज्ञात करने के लिए, हमें 84, 126 और 168 का महत्तम समापवर्तक (HCF) ज्ञात करना होगा।<br>अभाज्य गुणनखंडन:<br>84 = 2 &times; 2 &times; 3 &times; 7<br>126 = 2 &times; 3 &times; 3 &times; 7<br>168 = 2 &times; 2 &times; 2 &times; 3 &times; 7<br>उभयनिष्ठ गुणनखंड 2, 3 और 7 हैं।<br>HCF = 2 &times; 3 &times; 7 = 42.<br>अतः, प्रत्येक टुकड़े की अधिकतम संभव लंबाई 42 मीटर है।<br><br><b>Short Trick:</b><br>The lengths are 84, 126, 168.<br>Check difference: 126 - 84 = 42; 168 - 126 = 42.<br>42 perfectly divides 84, 126, and 168. So, HCF = 42.",
